Then $[AEDC] = [AEP] + [CEP].$  By the sine formula,
\begin{align*}
[AEP] &= \frac{1}{2} \cdot AE \cdot EP \cdot \sin \angle AEP \\
&= \frac{1}{2} \cdot \frac{2}{3} AD \cdot \frac{3}{2} \cdot \frac{2}{\sqrt{5}} \\
&= \frac{2 \sqrt{5}}{15} AD.
\end{align*}Similarly,
\[CEP = \frac{2 \sqrt{5}}{15} CE.\]Hence,
\[[AEDC] = \frac{2 \sqrt{5}}{15} (AD + CE) = \frac{2 \sqrt{5}}{15} \cdot \frac{4}{3} \sqrt{\frac{9}{4} - \frac{3}{16}} = \boxed{\frac{4 \sqrt{5}}{5}}.\]
